@Falck.Api_HostAddress = http://localhost:5229

### Login as seeded admin (full access) — copy the token into @token below
POST {{Falck.Api_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "Admin123!"
}

### Login as seeded read-only user (GET only)
POST {{Falck.Api_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user",
  "password": "User123!"
}

### Register a new account (always created as a read-only User)
POST {{Falck.Api_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "newuser",
  "password": "NewUser123!"
}

@token = PASTE_TOKEN_HERE

### List all employees (Admin or User)
GET {{Falck.Api_HostAddress}}/api/employees
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Get employee detail (history + projects) (Admin or User)
GET {{Falck.Api_HostAddress}}/api/employees/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Create an employee (Admin only)
POST {{Falck.Api_HostAddress}}/api/employees
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Pedro Salazar",
  "currentPosition": "Developer",
  "salary": 4500,
  "departmentId": 1
}

### Update an employee (promotion: position change updates the history) (Admin only)
PUT {{Falck.Api_HostAddress}}/api/employees/2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Carlos Pérez",
  "currentPosition": "Manager",
  "salary": 7000,
  "departmentId": 1
}

### Delete an employee (Admin only)
DELETE {{Falck.Api_HostAddress}}/api/employees/5
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List departments (Admin or User)
GET {{Falck.Api_HostAddress}}/api/departments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Section 4.3: employees of a department with at least one project (Admin or User)
GET {{Falck.Api_HostAddress}}/api/departments/1/employees-with-projects
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json
